Quote:  classer; wool classer: The key employee of the shed who classes the wool into grades according to quality before it is placed in the wool bins, and who is responsible for all processing after the fleece leaves the sheep's back. He is colloquially known as the `guesser' or `conman'.
Notes:  (Wallace Shearing Glossary)
